From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date: Tue, 16 Jun 2026 11:45:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] misc: configure Fruit Jam USB host PIO2 TX path

Configure the staged Pico-PIO-USB state machines on PIO2 and add a
bounded tx-test command that pushes a tiny encoded host packet through the
TX state machine. This is still not HID enumeration, but it proves Linux can
own the non-conflicting PIO2 block, configure GPIO1/GPIO2 for the packet
engine, and advance packet/error counters without pulling in the full USB
or input stacks.
---
 drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c | 311 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 306 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c
+++ b/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c
